Q1. Write a Python program to get the current time and demonstrate the following functions from the time module:        
a) Converts time in seconds to a struct_time in UTC  b) Converts a struct_time object into a formatted string. 

import time
current_seconds = time.time()
print("Current time in seconds:", current_seconds)
utc_time = time.gmtime(current_seconds)
print("UTC struct_time:", utc_time)
formatted_time = time.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S", utc_time)
print("Formatted UTC time:", formatted_time)


